import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

df = pd.read_csv("data/processed/music_culture_merged.csv")
df.head()

plt.figure()
plt.scatter(df["gdp_per_capita"], df["avg_popularity"])
plt.xlabel("GDP per capita (USD)")
plt.ylabel("Average Spotify popularity")
plt.title("GDP vs Spotify Popularity")
plt.show()

plt.figure()
plt.scatter(df["internet_users_pct"], df["avg_popularity"])
plt.xlabel("Internet users (% of population)")
plt.ylabel("Average Spotify popularity")
plt.title("Internet Access vs Spotify Popularity")
plt.show()

The scatterplots above show:

- A moderate positive relationship between GDP per capita and average Spotify
  popularity.
- A strong positive relationship between internet penetration and popularity.

These visual patterns are described in the README under *Findings*.

